cs. The Woman's Building offered female artists an unprecedented opportunity to create public art and imagine an historical narrative that put women rather than men at its center.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Jul 2020) 0aDecoration and ornament, ArchitecturalzIllinoiszChicagoxHistoryy19th centuryxThemes, motives. 0aMural painting and decorationzIllinoiszChicagoy19th centuryxThemes, motives. 0aSex role in art. 0aWomen artists. 0aWomen in art. 4a1893 columbian expedition. 4a19th century art. 4a19th century chicago. 4a19th century culture. 4a19th century history. 4a19th century women. 4aart at columbian expedition. 4aart criticism. 4aart herstory. 4aart history. 4aart. 4aartists. 4achicago worlds fair. 4acolumbian expedition chicago. 4ahistorical art. 4amurals. 4apaintings. 4apublic art. 4awhite city worlds fair. 4awhite city. 4awomans building 1893 columbian expedition. 4awomans building. 4awomen artists. 4awomen in art. 4awomens history. 4aworlds fair. 7aART / American / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024111440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520947467423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520947467.jpg  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles